Description: Handle sliver of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora to sharpish turn. Clay fine buff-brown; cream slip. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 206, 4 Name Aristakos. From the same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0065.30.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1083)
